snippet.textDisplay:
Why dont intel or AMD just make the CPU Die to where it has open air gaps in between each transister.
This, coupled with a non conductive thermal liquid loop could cool ( In theory ) a 2 nanometer chip. Given that the Gaps are 2nm wide allowing heat to escape naturally instead of being conducted through unnecessary Layers. This cooling measure could also be put to work on the CPUs we have now.
